			<div class="content" id="post-content-553177">
									

<p>Thankies. ^_^</p>
<p><strong>EDIT, 2015:</strong> Although this edit has <em>nothing</em> to do with the preceding post or the person who made it, I don't have any posts on this thread higher up than this one, and <em>I'd like for this message to get as much visibility as possible.</em></p>
<p>Obviously, anyone can make any kind of SCP-811-derivative work they wish to, so long as they abide by the Creative Commons license. However, I, the author, am personally uncomfortable with certain kinds of fan work and do not wish to see them. <strong>Please do not send me (Pig_catapult) links to any content sexualising SCP-811 in any way.</strong></p>
<p>For a non-hypothetical example: Linking me to a [website redacted] group dedicated to compiling SCP-811 fanart: Good! I get warm fuzzies seeing that people like SCP-811 enough to draw her. Linking me to a [website redacted] group dedicated to compiling SCP-811 fanart, with an emphasis on SCP-811's buttocks stated in the rules: Not good! That creeps me the fuck out. Please don't do it.</p>
<p><strong>Edit 2016:</strong> A quick note to translators: &quot;air-wee is&quot; is SCP-811 trying to approximate a word she doesn't know (&quot;earliest&quot;) with smaller words that she does know, and should probably not be translated literally.</p>
<p><strong>Edit 2017:</strong> I've made Aoshi's performance as Dr. Trebuchet's voice in <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bBqrrRz9Pac">this dramatic reading of the interview log</a> canon. That is how Dr. Trebuchet sounds.</p>
<p><strong>Edit also 2017:</strong> To elaborate on Edit 2015: Due to issues of both communication difficulties and emotional immaturity, <strong>SCP-811 is not capable of giving informed consent to sexual activities.</strong></p>
<p><strong>Edit 2018:</strong> Since I can think of three questions that have been asked frequently, on- and off-site, about this article, I've decided to add an</p>
<h1><span>FAQ</span></h1>
<p><strong>Q: Why is Watchel such a wuss? That's a pretty tame transformation/cannibalism description.</strong><br />
A: What turned Watchel's stomach wasn't the description in and of itself, but the full sequence of events <em>implied</em> by that description: A little girl is kidnapped by a man with a syringe, goes through a painful transformation in which she pukes out huge quantities of blood and some of her organs, is introduced to her new hands and new Horror Hunger by killing that man in her terror, and then, after either not seeking out help from a responsible adult or seeking help and <em>failing to receive it,</em> that little girl goes and lives alone as a cryptid monster in a swamp until the Foundation finds her, as a developmentally-impaired adult who at some point along the way stopped considering herself a person. In my mind, when Watchel went home that night, after what was his first time interviewing a humanoid SCP, he hugged his young daughter for a long time and cried. She's about the right age and has long dark hair.</p>
<p><strong>Q: Is SCP-811 based on <em>X</em>?</strong><br />
A: Unless <em>X</em> is &quot;the general idea of a humanoid swamp monster,&quot; no.</p>
<p><strong>Q: How do you pronounce &quot;Aé&quot;?</strong><br />
A: Ah-eh.</p>

